node.text: I’m a proud Houston woman— I’ve celebrated Juneteenth for many years, and its incredible to watch our Texan holiday become national. This holiday has always been about liberation. It’s our Independence Day and now it’s a federal holiday. It’s bittersweet because right now they are working to suppress black history in schools—ultimately erasing the negative effects of white supremacy in this country. How can we move forward if we can’t learn from our mistakes? As we celebrate Juneteenth officially as a nation today, remember to continue to fight against the systemic racism that holds us back from true progress. Love y’all!

🎫LAST CHANCE TO WIN TICKETS YALL🎫

The best part is that every entry helps me raise awareness and support for Black-led organizations. 

There’s only a few days left so enter now at lizzolovesyou.com
